text:
Student,.

emma23engel@gmail.com | My wikipedia page



Pursuing a Bachelors Degree in Data Science at Brigham Young University of Idaho.


Database Engineering, Data Administration, Apperal design, Photography




2016-2020 Shelley Senior High School, Shelley.
2020 - 2024 Brigham Young University of Idaho, Rexburg

Associates degree

2020 - now Brigham Young University of Idaho, Rexburg

Working towards Bachelors




MCWIT - Aspirations in computing Award


May 2024 - July 2024 BYU Employment ~ Provo, UT: Church Youth Camp Counselor (seasonal position) -Taught groups of youth, individually and with a Co-counselor.
-Promoted and maintained an uplifting environment aligned with a focus on helping participants grow socially, intellectually, and spiritually.
July 2024 - December 2024 Great Harvest ~ Idaho Falls, ID: Baker/Server/Prepper (seasonal position) -Prepped food and drink orders.
-Oversaw cash and credit interactions.
-prepared and baked the product.
August 2023 - October 2023 CinnaBear Bakery ~ Gardiner, MT: Server/Prepper (seasonal position) -Prepped food and drink orders.
-Oversaw cash and credit interactions.
July 2021 - December 2022 The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints ~ Fort Worth, TX: Volunteer Representative
-Trained new, incoming volunteers in the type of work done.
-Participated in leadership roles.
-Planned and carried out lessons for groups ranging from very large to individual basis.
May 2020 - August 2020 Snogo Shaved Ice ~ Shelley, ID: Server/Prepper (seasonal position) -Offered a promotion to manager after my first summer of working here.
-Managed workplace individually during shifts and oversaw cash and credit interactions.
May 2019 - August 2019 Apple Athletic Club ~ Idaho Falls, ID — Summer Day Camp Counselor (seasonal position) -Planned, organized, and facilitated camp activities for 50 kids for an entire week.
-Worked flexibly with co-workers to meet the needs of campers, parents, and gym members.
-Helped participants enjoy activities while ensuring adherence to protocol.




Student, Rexburg
